            A formal debate setup, with Supreme Commander's gown casting fire-and-water light. Professor Logic's tie begins to spark as he grapples with logic's limits. A quantum duck quacks syllogisms, and a tomato spawns a sheep in a philosopher's toga.
        </div>

        <div class="debate-section">
            <h3>üìê PROFESSOR LOGIC'S OPENING üìê</h3>
            
            <div class="character">
                <span class="character-name">PROFESSOR LOGIC:</span>
                <div class="dialogue">(adjusting perfectly straight tie) "From first principles, logic is a formal system for determining validity of inferences. It operates independently of context and produces consistent, reproducible conclusions. Logic is, by definition, not subjective."</div>
            </div>

            <div class="character">
                <span class="character-name">PROFESSOR LOGIC:</span>
                <div class="dialogue">"Reason, by contrast, is a broader cognitive process that incorporates logical operations but extends beyond them. The critical distinction: Logic asks 'Is this inference valid?' Reason asks 'What should I believe given available evidence, context, and goals?'"</div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="stage-direction">
            Captain Quantum suddenly appears, quantum duck in tow.
        </div>

        <div class="character">
            <span class="character-name">CAPTAIN QUANTUM:</span>
            <div class="dialogue">(floating) "Logic's the skeleton; reason's the dance! Like my duck, quacking in all possible logical boxes simultaneously!"</div>
        </div>

        <div class="character">
            <span class="character-name">PROFESSOR LOGIC:</span>
            <div class="dialogue">(tie beginning to <span class="tie-malfunction">spark</span>) "Your duck metaphor introduces unnecessary imprecision. Ducks cannot exist in quantum superposition at macroscopic scales."</div>
        </div>

        <div class="logic-fail">
            <h3>‚ö†Ô∏è LOGIC ENCOUNTERS PARADOX ‚ö†Ô∏è</h3>
            
            <div class="character">
                <span class="character-name">DR. BRIDGE:</span>
                <div class="dialogue">(sketching frantically) "Professor, your logic is trying to solve an infinite recursion problem with finite steps! It's like counting quantum ducks while they're laying quantum eggs!"</div>
            </div>

            <div class="character">
                <span class="character-name">PROFESSOR LOGIC:</span>
                <div class="dialogue">(tie now <span class="tie-malfunction">visibly sparking</span>) "The... the mathematical framework requires... recursive self-reference that... this is highly irregular..."</div>
            </div>

            <div class="character">
                <span class="character-name">CAPTAIN QUANTUM:</span>
                <div class="dialogue">(grinning) "Professor, you're discovering what we learned long ago - some problems require leap-of-faith solutions rather than step-by-step proofs!"</div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="character">
            <span class="character-name">SUPREME COMMANDER:</span>
            <div class="dialogue">(tossing tomato, spawning philosopher sheep) "Logic's mundane compared to reason! Logic gives us 'If A then B.' Reason gives us 'Maybe A is dancing with C while B takes a nap!' Our Academy will teach both to waltz together!"</div>
        </div>

        <div class="debate-section">
            <h3>üåÄ THE COSMIC REVELATION üåÄ</h3>
            
            <div class="character">
